gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 129, Bucks 122
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Bucks, 129-122. The Knicks had four players scoring 20+ points, Jalen Brunson leading the way with 38 points and six assists.  Julius Randle (24 points, nine rebounds), RJ Barrett (21 points, six rebounds), and Immanuel Quickley (20 points) combined for 65 points. Giannis Antetokounmpo led Milwaukee with 32 points, 13 rebounds, and six assists as Damian Lillard (32 points, eight assists) and Khris Middleton (24 points, six assists) totaled 56 points. The Knicks snap a 7-game win streak for the Bucks and improve to 17-12 as the Bucks move to 22-8.
